Reply cmt.Cmt: Huy Nguyen ông bị lag à?
Long Hoàng 🤷lag gì ở đây

In a word, yes, cows' milk is bad for cats. Most cats are actually 'lactose intolerant' as they don't have the enzyme (lactase) in their intestines to digest the sugar in milk (lactose), meaning that milk which contains lactose can make them poorly.

Long Hoàng Is it OK to feed cats cow's milk?
The truth is that most cats are lactose intolerant so giving them cow's milk can actually cause significant health issues. Milk doesn't part of necessary cat nutrition and many cats suffer stomach upsets or other related problems because their owner thought that they were giving them a treat.
